dc_title_s: Public surveys in the state of Wisconsin and territory of Minnesota.
dc_description_s: Shows all of Wisconsin and a portion of Minnesota, with township surveys in progress in portions of west-central Wisconsin; blank townships drawn on part of the "Menominee Cession of Oct. 18th, 1848."   Includes legend explaining symbols for township suvey status on map.   At head of title:(A).   Appeared as House Executive Document no. 5, 31st Congress, 1st Session.|48 x 59 centimeters|Scale 1:1,140,480 18 miles to an inch|General Map Collection
dc_publisher_s: United States Surveyor General's Office (Dubuque, Iowa)
